column2: Has rained for last week and half.
Very little boating or water skiing on the lake.  Some algae bloom.  Clear day.
Lake activity low- not much boating or skiing.
Lake activity very low.  Fishing but no skiing.  The sun is bright- the air temperature is 50 degrees- and the temperature at night is 38 degrees- cool nights.
Water level: Up from last testing
First day there was sun + didn't have much wind in many a day.  Water was clearest since early spring.
Some algae and bright to cloudy bright.
Public perception 3 for swimming due to schistome.  One of summer's best !
Murky water/possibly from high winds.  Bright day-low humidity/2 days ago.
Water temp. 70 degrees-some algae-a good day in the north woods. gentle south wind.
Perfect weather- calm- sunny- algae bloom on 8/16/96.
Sunny and the wind is 5-10 mph.
Rain gauge reading from 6/16 to 7/17 = 3 3/8 inches.
Rain gauge reading from 7/18 to 8/21 = 4.5 inches.
Rain gauge reading from 8/21 to 10/16 = 6.75 inches.  Surface of water is foamy.
Clear northeast wind at 5 mph.  The temperature is 54 degrees.
Additional volunteer Jackie Fruth(85481) 3mph wind from the S. West partly cloudy with some sun.
Slight Bloom at this location but not as much as Ne Basin weather same.
winds 7 mph. not much activity boats-etc.
overcast day SW winds 5-7 mph. slight chop. sighting 1 loon near boat 2 fishing boats
pollen floating in the water lots of fishing boats- sunny very calm 5 m.p.h.

column1: No wild life very queit lake activity

column2: pollen in the water leaving the water a bit murky looking saw 1 loon and 2 fishing boats very calm wind 3 mph.
very calm day / bloom on North Twin / spotted 1 loon
pollen present SE. winds 5-7 mph partly sunny

column1: not alot of activity on the lake

column2: Saw one loon right in front of our boat- a few fisherman but not alot of activity. Weather was partly cloudy and a bit of a chop on the water. All in all a good day for lake monitoring
not alot of activity/ very clear
NorthEast Winds 7 mph. Very sunny skies some pollem in the water. Stormed the night before 3/4 inch of rain Fishing and SkiingBoats- Beautiful Clear Day saw 3 loons swimming together   Some boating
Winds are picking up partly sunny skies. Rain the night before. Not much activity on the lake
Sunny with thin clouds. Surface temperature 67 degrees. No rain for 2 days!
Sunny and clear. 3 inch chop. Water temperature 74.7 degrees F.
3 inch chop. Partly sunny- water temp 55 degrees F-

6 inch chop- mostly cloudy- water temp 75 degrees F- cold front.
